title: Warning: Inconsistent state! Dependent hash1 of hash2 not in DB
body:
I tried uninstalling all of my Spack packages, and they successfully uninstalled, but the above warning message was printed hundreds of times.

### Spack version

```console
$ spack --version
0.14.1-440-864960937d
```

### Steps to reproduce the issue

```console
$ spack uninstall -a
```

### Error Message

The first 30 or so packages uninstall smoothly, but after that I see the "inconsistent state" warning message growing exponentially. It's almost like we're uninstalling packages in the wrong order. I can't help but feel like this is related to #3690. See below for log.
